WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:03.810
- Imagine your boss says
to you, "We need to talk."

2
00:00:03.810 --> 00:00:05.340
A little worrying, right?

3
00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:09.390
Now, imagine a coworker
says, "We need to talk."

4
00:00:09.390 --> 00:00:12.390
Same words, different reaction.

5
00:00:12.390 --> 00:00:14.580
You can sense the difference
between those situations

6
00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:18.450
because you understand nuance,
context and consequences

7
00:00:18.450 --> 00:00:20.790
but AI can't understand those things,

8
00:00:20.790 --> 00:00:22.650
not on its own at least.

9
00:00:22.650 --> 00:00:24.510
It can be an amazing collaborator

10
00:00:24.510 --> 00:00:27.570
and help you enhance your
work in all sorts of ways

11
00:00:27.570 --> 00:00:30.660
but AI doesn't live in
the real world like we do.

12
00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:34.830
That means you need to
exercise responsible AI use.

13
00:00:34.830 --> 00:00:37.620
This is a big part of
our work here at Google.

14
00:00:37.620 --> 00:00:40.410
We're committed to AI that
encourages bold innovation,

15
00:00:40.410 --> 00:00:43.860
responsible development
and collaborative progress.

16
00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:46.530
These are AI principles.

17
00:00:46.530 --> 00:00:48.990
So knowing AI's limitations

18
00:00:48.990 --> 00:00:52.110
enables you to use it more
effectively and responsibly.

19
00:00:52.110 --> 00:00:54.960
For example, AI can get things wrong

20
00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:58.260
and say things that aren't
true or suddenly false.

21
00:00:58.260 --> 00:01:00.570
This is called hallucination.

22
00:01:00.570 --> 00:01:04.260
There are many reasons
why AI may hallucinate.

23
00:01:04.260 --> 00:01:07.500
For one, it may be that its
underlying training data

24
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:09.060
has an error.

25
00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:10.860
It could also be that it's
trying to solve a problem

26
00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:14.760
that's entirely too unique and
that it hasn't seen before.

27
00:01:14.760 --> 00:01:16.800
Might also struggle to
accurately understand

28
00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.800
real world knowledge and physical things

29
00:01:19.800 --> 00:01:22.650
or it might be because it's
trying to create an answer

30
00:01:22.650 --> 00:01:24.390
but it's really just a guess.

31
00:01:24.390 --> 00:01:26.160
Because AI can hallucinate,

32
00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:29.100
you always need to pay attention
and verify what you get

33
00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:30.720
before using it in your work,

34
00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:32.940
even if the responses sound confident.

35
00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:34.770
Another limitation you should be aware of

36
00:01:34.770 --> 00:01:38.610
is that AI does not have
common sense like you and me.

37
00:01:38.610 --> 00:01:42.000
And while its outputs can
seem insightful or intuitive,

38
00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:43.080
you have to remember

39
00:01:43.080 --> 00:01:46.380
that it doesn't have a real
understanding of the world.

40
00:01:46.380 --> 00:01:47.213
At the end of the day,

41
00:01:47.213 --> 00:01:49.620
its outputs are just based on
patterns it learned from data,

42
00:01:49.620 --> 00:01:51.360
not real experience.

43
00:01:51.360 --> 00:01:53.910
For instance, recently, I
asked it about street festivals

44
00:01:53.910 --> 00:01:55.830
in an upcoming weekend.

45
00:01:55.830 --> 00:01:58.560
It pulled street festivals
from previous years.

46
00:01:58.560 --> 00:02:02.010
It was a mistake but I
caught it and corrected it.

47
00:02:02.010 --> 00:02:04.680
So what part do you play as an AI user?

48
00:02:04.680 --> 00:02:06.810
Well, you're in the driver's seat.

49
00:02:06.810 --> 00:02:09.540
You're responsible for overseeing
each step of the process

50
00:02:09.540 --> 00:02:11.490
from beginning to end.

51
00:02:11.490 --> 00:02:13.710
We call this human-in-the-loop

52
00:02:13.710 --> 00:02:15.660
meaning you should be constantly involved

53
00:02:15.660 --> 00:02:17.940
with the use of AI at each step.

54
00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:20.790
Now, the need to use AI
responsibly is pretty obvious

55
00:02:20.790 --> 00:02:22.417
but you may be thinking to yourself,

56
00:02:22.417 --> 00:02:24.810
"How do I do this," or "Where do I start?"

57
00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:26.520
Well, there are three simple steps

58
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:29.610
to making sure you're
using AI responsibly.

59
00:02:29.610 --> 00:02:31.920
To remember it, we like
to use the term ACT

60
00:02:31.920 --> 00:02:34.200
for ACT responsibly.

61
00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:36.810
A stands for ask.

62
00:02:36.810 --> 00:02:39.517
Before doing anything, ask yourself,

63
00:02:39.517 --> 00:02:42.150
"Is this even a case where
I should be using AI?"

64
00:02:42.150 --> 00:02:45.630
For example, don't rely
on responses as medical,

65
00:02:45.630 --> 00:02:47.940
legal, financial or other
professional advice.

66
00:02:47.940 --> 00:02:50.850
Always consult a
professional on these topics.

67
00:02:50.850 --> 00:02:52.950
If your task involves sensitive,

68
00:02:52.950 --> 00:02:56.160
confidential, personal
or proprietary data,

69
00:02:56.160 --> 00:02:58.440
consider whether or not you should use AI.

70
00:02:58.440 --> 00:03:00.667
Another question you
should ask yourself is,

71
00:03:00.667 --> 00:03:02.940
"Can I use an off the shelf solution,"

72
00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:05.670
or "Is it better suited
for an enterprise tool?"

73
00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:08.130
You should always consult
your employer's policies

74
00:03:08.130 --> 00:03:09.270
on using AI at work

75
00:03:09.270 --> 00:03:13.500
and avoid inputting confidential
data into a public AI tool.

76
00:03:13.500 --> 00:03:17.400
Next up, C which stands for check.

77
00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:19.800
After you've decided that
AI is right for the task,

78
00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.110
check the outputs before using them.

79
00:03:22.110 --> 00:03:24.990
First, check for objectivity.

80
00:03:24.990 --> 00:03:26.640
Remember that a model's training data

81
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:29.250
can sometimes produce unintended results.

82
00:03:29.250 --> 00:03:30.690
It's your responsibility

83
00:03:30.690 --> 00:03:33.240
to critically review the AI's response.

84
00:03:33.240 --> 00:03:35.610
This involves looking out
for one-sided arguments,

85
00:03:35.610 --> 00:03:37.470
loaded language, stereotypes

86
00:03:37.470 --> 00:03:41.010
or other unfair assumptions
that AI may have learned.

87
00:03:41.010 --> 00:03:44.220
Next, check for accuracy.

88
00:03:44.220 --> 00:03:45.930
Verify the outputs you receive

89
00:03:45.930 --> 00:03:47.610
and make sure that any information

90
00:03:47.610 --> 00:03:51.330
which is presented as factual actually is.

91
00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:52.500
When checking your outputs,

92
00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:55.170
you also wanna look out for bias.

93
00:03:55.170 --> 00:03:56.100
In many cases,

94
00:03:56.100 --> 00:03:58.380
it's what you do with
the output that matters.

95
00:03:58.380 --> 00:03:59.670
You should always check

96
00:03:59.670 --> 00:04:02.850
that the output is appropriate
for its intended use.

97
00:04:02.850 --> 00:04:04.980
You should not rely on
AI to finish work for you

98
00:04:04.980 --> 00:04:06.660
without your oversight.

99
00:04:06.660 --> 00:04:09.240
Completing the task requires your judgment

100
00:04:09.240 --> 00:04:10.680
and accountability.

101
00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:14.100
Finally, T stands for tell.

102
00:04:14.100 --> 00:04:15.900
Being a responsible AI user

103
00:04:15.900 --> 00:04:18.270
involves disclosing your use of it.

104
00:04:18.270 --> 00:04:21.180
Always be transparent
about your use of AI.

105
00:04:21.180 --> 00:04:23.580
One way that Google is helping
to increase transparency

106
00:04:23.580 --> 00:04:26.340
of AI use is with SynthID,

107
00:04:26.340 --> 00:04:28.560
a new tool which adds digital watermarks

108
00:04:28.560 --> 00:04:31.350
into AI-generated content like videos

109
00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:34.320
so the use of AI can be detected easily.

110
00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:37.140
Okay, we've covered all parts of ACT.

111
00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:39.420
Before you use AI, ask yourself

112
00:04:39.420 --> 00:04:42.540
whether or not the tool
is right for the task,

113
00:04:42.540 --> 00:04:45.870
check all AI-generated
outputs before using them

114
00:04:45.870 --> 00:04:48.990
and when you do, tell people.

115
00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:50.610
And remember, it's up to you

116
00:04:50.610 --> 00:04:53.130
to be the human-in-the-loop at each step.

117
00:04:53.130 --> 00:04:54.843
Now you're ready to keep going.